# What is Computer Science Fundamentals?

Computer Science Fundamentals are courses for elementary students in grades K-5. Are you familiar with Code.org's <a href="https://code.org/learn" > **Hour of Code** </a>?

Computer Science Fundamentals courses and Hour of Code are not the same thing. Hour of Code *introduces* students to computer science while Computer Science Fundamentals courses ***build and strengthen*** computer science knowledge and skills.

## Why teach Computer Science Fundamentals?

* Supports both pre-readers and readers.
* Aligned to K12 Computer Science Framework practices and CSTA K-12 standards.
* Includes cross-curricular activities mapped to ELA/Math Common Core State Standards and Next Generation Science Standards.
* **Does not require you or your students to have any prior knowledge or skills in computer science.**

